    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.52/586</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1552</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt of your
                    despatch, No. 3693, of February 25, 1921,<note n="93" xml:id="d411fn93">Not
                        printed.</note> …</p>
                <p>With respect to this law<note n="94" xml:id="d411fn94">Law of Dec. 28,
                        1920.</note> you are directed to point out informally to the appropriate
                    authorities that it does not seem to provide for the establishment of adequate
                    machinery for ascertaining and paying the compensation properly due to owners
                    whose land is expropriated, and that it seems possible that under this law
                    property might be taken without proper provision being made for
                    compensation.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry P. Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
